<br>
A: The WS will outdamage the lammy until you reach the low 40s. You should switch after that. <br>
<br>
Why? In lower levels the better ratio on the WS allows it to outdamage the lammy. Warriors get a raw damage bonus added to each hit from the primary hand. This damage bonus increases with levels. Once a warrior reaches the mid 40s the damage bonus plus the fast speed of the lammy combine to outperform the Wurmslayer.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that the WS will have lowsy aggro and you'll annoy many a rogue by using it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A> at: 4/17/02 10:05:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushikariiapoccalypse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 1236<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 9:09:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2403.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Q: Haste vs Haste</span><hr size=1> Q: I have no haste, or a lesser haste item and want to Upgrade. What is Better ?        <br>
<br>
A: Haste is very Valuable to a Warrior. It is worth losing AC over; and as you level it becomes more and more important. So you are looking for your First Haste item; you're around level 30 or so ( for arguement's sake ). Arguably the most common haste item that 99% of all warriors wore at one time was a FBSS; or a flowing black silk sash for the non-acronym types <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . Is it worth the AC/stat loss over; for example; straw spun belt; BA belt; or TBB ? Yes. Haste will increase the amount of times you swing during a fight; and thus increasing your position on a monsters hate list. No matter what AC you have; it does nothing if you're not getting hit.<br>
<br>
Next; upgrading haste. What is good to look for when upgrading haste items ?<br>
Obviously haste percentage. Other stats incluce AC, STR/STA/DEX/AGI and possibly resists where applicable; but to make the most of upgrading you should look for speed. Upgrading from a FBSS to; for example; Belt of Contention is a good thing ( gain 10 AC +str/sta and FR ); but compared to the likes of a RBB or RBG you'll clearly be getting a great upgrade in speed + stats since the FBSS and BoC are the same haste speed.<br>
<br>
Belt, Back, Head, or Glove Haste; what to choose ?<br>
Whatever you can get/afford. Look at the slots; and look at what is available to you. Back Haste items more often than not are near top-end Dragon Haste speed items; and complimented with a heavy AC/Stat Belt ( axgoreth belt ) you'll make AC and stat increases by leaps and bounds. But; also with Waist items ( RBB or RBG ); duo it up with a Seahorse Cape or chetari shield and you'll end up near; if not identical; Stat increases. The question of where you should stick your haste item is totally individual depending on what is available to you. Most people aren't in the position to have a Cloak of Flames or Cape of Crystalline Waters available to them; but if you do than filling your Waist slot with a haste item shouldn't be too much of a problem. But from a monetary and availability standpoint waist-slot haste is your Best friend. Make the most of it. **<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> added</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->** also with many newer patches in EQ; Silver Chitin Hand Wraps also provide a very nice haste percentage, decent affordability; and it frees up your waist and back slot for Heavy AC or HP items. Head-worn Haste Items also provide the same benefits; but are basically only available in the high-end EQ game ( minus the hangman's noose, off named flower Hangman in Trak's Teeth ) and at that point you can pretty much figure out your best items to fill the remaining slots you've freed up ( hamd/back/waist).<br>
<br>
Should I ever sell off a haste item to make for better AC ?<br>
Unless you have another haste item; <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Never Ever Ever Sell a Haste Item unless you have an Upgrade. Ever!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Losing haste is close to the worst things you can do to yourself; and the loss of haste is something you'll feel the second you fight something. So what if you're level 60 and still own a FBSS. You're still 21% faster than you'd be without it.<br>
<br>
