<br>
A: Generally, you'll want to pick armor that has high AC, HP, and/or stamina. There is a supposed AC soft cap around 1200-1300 AC, so you'll be best off picking raw HP items as opposed to AC items once you reach 1200 AC. Until then, you can use the old rule of thumb - 1 AC = 10 HP.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Q: Crafted or Crusty - which is better?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: Generally, Crustacean is, especially at higher levels when you get more HP per point of stamina. However, some pieces of Crafted are rather nice. Mixing and matching Crafted and Crusty is a smart way to go.<br>
<br>
Crustacean Shell Boots +10AC +6Str +12Sta -2Dex -5Cha<br>
Crustacean Shell Bracers +9AC +5Str +4Sta -5Cha <br>
Crustacean Shell Breastplate +19 AC +5Str +15Sta -8Cha<br>
Crustacean Shell Gauntlets +11AC +8Str -5Cha <br>
Crustacean Shell Greaves +12AC +4Str +16Sta -4Dex -4Cha<br>
Crustacean Shell Helm +12AC +10Sta -5Cha <br>
Crustacean Shell Shield +17AC +4Str +10Sta -7Cha <br>
Crustacean Shell Vambraces +10AC +8Str +12Sta -4Dex -4Cha <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Q: Warlord's or Myrmidon's - which is better?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: Depends on what you want. Overall, Warlord's is superior in regards to AC and stamina, while Myrmidon's has an edge in raw HP and resists. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A> at: 5/10/02 3:16:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uraaj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raaj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 12:48:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2403.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://raaj.freewebspace.com/sigs/personalpic.gif width=104 height=143></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Q: Haste vs Haste</span><hr size=1> Q: What weapons agro best?<br>
<br>
A: Weapons with debuffs, slows, stuns, or straight hate. IE: Frostbringer (ac debuff), Willsapper (slow), SoD(stun), Blade of Carnage (hate)<br>
<br>
Q: 2h or 1h?<br>
<br>
A: Depending on your weapons, if they're around the same level of item, 2h will generally outdamage 1h, but its easier to hold agro while defensive with a pair of 1h's. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8921">Raaj Solumnus</a> <<a href="http://www.clantaveren.com">Clan Ta Veren</a>>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uthehavocblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheHavocblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 12:06:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2403.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Q: Crafted/Crusty upgrade.</span><hr size=1> Q:  I'm in crusty and crafted, looking to upgrade...what next?<br>
<br>
A:  Look into buying/camping some cobalt pieces (locations below), or, if your guild is capable, raiding Kael Drakkel for Thurgadin quest armors.<br>
<br>
Cobalt Locations:  Gloves:  Karnor's Castle, Drolvarg Captain.  Boots:  Karnor's Castle, Caller of Sathir.  Cobalt Arms:  Sebilis, Froglok Zol Knights.  Cobalt Bracer: Sebilis, Myconid Reavers  Cobalt Helm: Sebilis, Reet Knights  Cobalt Greaves:  Karnor's Castle, Venril Sathir.  Cobalt Breastplate:  Sebilis, Trakanon<br>
<br>
The most common (and affordable) pieces of cobalt are Gauntlets, Boots, and Vambraces...Bracers and Helms are very rare drops off of the higher level mobs in Seb, and the BP and Greaves come off of raid-type mobs.<br>
<br>
Thurgadin armor component locations:  Kael Drakkel, either the Arena area (very low drop rate), the Tormax ramp area (somewhat more common than arena, still not great), or Iceshard manor, also known as the Icehouse, Platehouse, Shard, etc. from server to server...only plate drops, fairly common through the cycle of giants spawned by a portion of the 9th coldain ring quest.<br>
<br>
Velious armor gems for Warriors:  BP: flawless diamond...Legs: Flawed Sea Sapphire...Arms: Flawed Emerald...Helm: Crushed Coral...Bracer:  Crushed Flame Emerald...Boots:  Crushed Black Marble...Gauntlets:  Crushed Topaz<br>
<br>
(edit:  thanks Adex for clearing up the cobalt helm/bracer mobs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uthehavocblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheHavocblade</A> at: 4/21/02 10:44:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utenasi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenasi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 11:24:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2403.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Warrior utility items</span><hr size=1> Q:  What regen items are there available for warriors, and what is the value of regen items?<br>
<br>
A:  There are 4 known tradeable regeneration items (innate, not casted, not counting Aura of Battle items) that can be warrior equipped.  They are:<br>
<br>
  1.  Rubicite Breastplate (3hp per tick)<br>
  2.  Iksar Ceremonial Chestplate (5hp per tick)<br>
  3.  Fungal Covered Tunic (15hp per tick)<br>
  4.  Heart of Fungus (10hp per tick)<br>
<br>
There are also several tradeable items with Aura of Battle (stackable, 2 pts regen per tick), as well as several no drop versions such as BP of the Vindicator.<br>
<br>
As far as value, your own server economy may vary completely, but for the most part you'll find the order of ascending values to be Iksar, Rubicite, Fungal, Heart.  Iksar is the most common, and limited to most chain classes.  Rubicite is also limited to chain classes, but rarer since it no longer drops.  Fungal tunics are very costly since they can be worn by most leather wearers and up, and have the highest AC/regen, though a few negative statistics.  Heart of Fungus can be equipped by all tank classes, have immense negative statistics, but are very-very-very rare...and relatively new, so expensive.<br>
<br>
Debate as to the value of innate regeneration items will always come down to what you get out of the item.  The trade-off between 15hp per tick and an extra 50-60ac and 100hp will only be valuable when in a raid/MT situation...while regen is much more valuable to a secondary tank/hybrid in a non-MT situation, especially with random damage such as AE's.<br>
<br>
<br>
Q:  What are some good 'snaring' items for warriors?<br>
<br>
A:  There are several different weapons and items that can proc or effect a snare upon a target.  There is also one right clickable charged item from Fungus Grove callers, and another from Stonebrunt Mts.  The proc'ing weapons that have a mob ensnaring effect are (in no particular order):<br>
<br>
   1.  Silken Whip of Ensnaring<br>
   2.  Anklesmasher<br>
   3.  Kunzar Ku'juch<br>
   4.  Tserrina's Whip<br>
<br>
<br>
Q:  What slowing weapons are available for warriors?<br>
<br>
A:  There are few slowing weapons known that are warrior equippable:<br>
<br>
   1.  Truncheon of Doom (Froglok Armsman)<br>
   2.  Wavecrasher (Shimmering Sea Spirit)<br>
   3.  Willsapper (Vaniki)<br>
   4.  Trident of the Deep Sea (Lord Koi'Doken)<br>
   5.  Canyoneer's Pike ('a canyoneer' in Droga)<br>
<br>
